amending sections 3 and 4 of this act to provide for an advisory committee of law enforcement to study best methods to combat violent drug traffic and its effect on our citizens.  Section 4(a) of the bill authorizes the Secretary of Homeland Security, in consultation with the Attorney General, to establish a community-based interdiction program pursuant to the Department's drug interdiction strategy.  Currently, the Secretary is required by law to develop an interdiction strategy which is ``based on the best available science and existing programs.''  Section 3 of this act provides that the Secretary shall report back to Congress on this interdiction strategy for review of the interdiction strategy.  Section 4(b) of the bill provides that the Assistant Secretary of Homeland Security for Public Protection and Security may advise the Secretary on implementation of the interdiction strategy which will be promulgated by the Secretary under the authority of section 4 of the bill. 
